    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-09-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-09-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="316" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d316">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Arriaga</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 20,
                                    1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to our conversation this
                            forenoon, I have the honor to inform you that the so-called reciprocity
                            arrangement between the United States and Guatemala was based on the
                            third section of the statute known as the McKinley law, which was
                            repealed by the going into effect of our existing tariff law, at
                            midnight on the 27th ultimo.</p>
                <p>This is in accordance with the opinion of the Secretary of the Treasury,
                            in which I concur.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
